{
  "text": "where \u2202 x (.) and \u2202 y (.) are gradients in horizontal and vertical direction respectively. Similar to previous works [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , we assume that the image edges are very good indicator of scene discontinuity, however we use them to guide the normal smoothness. Eqn. (5) allows for normal discontinuities at the areas where strong image gradient is present while penalizing the normal discontinuities in the homogeneous regions of the image.",
